cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about machine-learning based dialogue managers, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different policies and architectures for dialogue management, which involves decision-making and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms to learn complex behaviors and generalize to new domains suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper also introduces a new architecture with a memory component and attention mechanism, which involves neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture on a dialogue task, which involves testing and evaluation, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category as well.
